				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It has occured to me while levelling up a necro alt that this class is able to deal with higher mob DPS than mages are.
<br />

<br />
The scenario: A hard-hitting mob that summons, so no real kiting possible, one mages will need to chain both heals for the pet to tank. 
<br />

<br />
Setups: 23% spell haste for both mage and necro, 30% MR nuke focus, 7% crits on necro. Mage spec 200 conjuration, necro spec 100 alteration. 15% general MP.
<br />

<br />
Mage: Cycling PR and TER for 2100 HP healed in roughly 15.3 seconds, a little less than 140 0DPS, for a mana cost of ((300+400)*0.72) = 504, or 198 per tick. A little less than 100 DPS likely done from pet with DS on. Mage is 100% unable to nuke while chaining heals, so no more DPS than the pet.
<br />
Heal per second: ~ 140
<br />
Mana cost per tick: ~ 200
<br />
DPS: ~90
<br />

<br />
Necro: Letting pet attack from back while chaining <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3032&source=Live" target="_blank">http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3032&source=Live</a> (Touch of Mujaki) on the mob with themselves as tanks. In the theoretical scenario assuming no interrupts, the casting cycles will be (3.2*0.77) + 2.25 ~ 4.7 seconds. 
<br />
Average amount healed: 850 * (1 + 0.155(from nuke focus) + 0.04(from crits) ~ 1015. 
<br />
Heal per second: 1015 / 4.7 ~ 215
<br />
Mana cost per tick: ~440 - 50(lich) ~ 390
<br />
DPS: 215 + ~60(pet) ~ 275
<br />

<br />
Necro and mage facing random_dragon with 32k HP and 150 DPS:
<br />

<br />
Necro time spent: 32000 / 275 ~ 2 minutes
<br />
Necro HP: Never any problem
<br />

<br />
Mage time spent: ~6 minutes
<br />
Mage pet HP: Steadily decreasing at a pace of 10 / second, but still winning the fight since it has only lost 3.6k HP after the 6 minutes.
<br />

<br />
Let's give the dragon 200 DPS:
<br />

<br />
Necro scenario remains the same
<br />

<br />
Mage pet HP: Steadily decreasing at a pace of 60 / second, which means it would need roughly 21.5k HP to win the fight. The pet "LoH" will of course not change the losing outcome.
<br />

<br />
We picked the wrong class.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597626">Enharjaren Fenrirsbane</a> 
<br />
Arch Overseers
<br />
Bristlebane
<br />

