				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Weird, I made another reply in this thread, but it's gone now. Anyway, to answer Kirium:
<br />

<br />
The pet damage mitigation upgrade cut off roughly 20% of the damage done on my pet with the pet focus I had at that time - MoE. I did a quick parse to compare my own and my air pet's tanking just now, me with full tanking AA's but neglible worn effects, +8 avoidance and 1% shielding.
<br />

<br />
RS air pet got hit 60.5% of the time for 37.1% on average, taking 32.6 DPS.
<br />

<br />
I got hit 75% of the time for 45% on average, taking 47.8 DPS - the pet hence took around 70% of the damage I took tanking.
<br />

<br />
Full necro lifetap crit AA's are probably around 15%, though hard to find any parse, and DD crits 18%. If they have 45% MR focus too, this will mean around 280 heal per second given the ideal scenario. Let's cover the fact that they as int casters don't tank as well as the high focus mage pets, multiply it with 70% to get the damage the same mob would have done on the mage air pet, and you arrive at covering the equivalent of 200 DPS being done on the pet.
<br />

<br />
The fact remains that necros are way stronger even taking mobs head on. I myself often wonder why people reply  to posts when they don't even understand the matter being discussed.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597626">Enharjaren Fenrirsbane</a> 
<br />
Arch Overseers
<br />
Bristlebane
<br />

<br />
