			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Your figure for blood ravens seems very weird. I just made another quick parse, limited in duration since I don't have a healer around right now, and found similar values for this mob. My pet was taking around 63 DPS from a random blood raven in PoN, with me taking 86 DPS - pet took 73% of what I did. If your pet only took 38 DPS from a mob that triples for 266, I really would like to share your pet focus.. though I'm more inclined to think you were missing a lot of melee messages when parsing instead.
<br />

<br />
I can with good certainty say that you can expect an RS focused air pet to take around 70-75% of the damage an int caster takes, with a pet focus matching his own gear. This also given my lack of defensive bonuses - someone going heavily for shielding and +avoidance will of course get closer to the pet in tanking ability, an option open to necromancer tanks.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597626">Enharjaren Fenrirsbane</a> 
