			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If your RS Air pet is taking 63dps against Blood Ravens then you are doing something wrong. 
<br />

<br />
You did actually bother to have the pet attack the mob didn't you and not just have it on Pet Hold and let it get beat on?
<br />

<br />
I can say with complete certainty that my pet takes far less damage than I would if I was tanking it. Whilst it wouldn't be the drop from 98dps to 38dps that I posted above because when I measured the 98dps I never had a pet attacking at all as I didn't want to skew the results with pet stuns and stuff that necro pets don't get. I could have used a Water Pet and that wouldn't have modified the Blood Raven DPS at all as none of its attacks cause an increase in mob delay, but the aim when I was tanking was to measure mob DPS not kill the mob.
<br />

<br />
If you actually measure what delay Blood Ravens have then its 20 base delay, when using an Air or MS4 pet to tank them the mob delay increases to 31. If you are just sticking your pet on Pet Hold then I can see why you are getting odd results as the mob will be attacking with a delay of 20 rather than a delay of 31 which is what happens when its actually been tanked by the pet rather than just beat on the pet. This would result in a 55% increase in damage to the pet (or convert my 38dps into 59dps, rather close to your figure which makes me think this is what is happening).
<br />

<br />
Also I don't appreciate been told that I cannot parse just because what I claim doesn't agree with what you claim. 15 years experience as a PhD Experimental Physicist suggests I do have some clue as to how to record and analyse data in an unbiased fashion.
<br />

<br />
Incidentally for a much fuller analyse of comparing how various pets tank (against Blood Ravens) then see this thread
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13760" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13760</a><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
Cestus Dei
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
